 Armed policemen have taken over Jabi Lake Mall Abuja ahead of a planned protest and occupation of Shoprite by human rights activists to retaliate the xenophobic attacks on Nigerians in South Africa.Human and vehicular movement has been restricted within and outside the area as shoppers and shop owners in the mall were asked to pass through the exit gate.Â As of the time of this report, the protesters have not arrived but journalists have stationed their cameras for the coverage of the protest.